snippet.textDisplay: Covid19 is certainly serious, and the current social distancing measures being taken are necessary. But one thing to consider- the reason mortality rates may seem so much higher than the flu right now is precisely because it is a new virus. That is to say, we have a very small sample size of confirmed infected patients. And the people who are confirmed to have it are also the same people more likely to be hospitalized due to having more severe symptoms/dying from the virus. As more people are tested and found to have the virus, I think we will find that the death rate is not nearly as high as we currently think it is.
snippet.textOriginal: Covid19 is certainly serious, and the current social distancing measures being taken are necessary.
